$ Oracle SQL function: STANDARD_HASH
@ standard_hash

code {
select
   standard_hash(sysdate)            sha1_implicit,
   standard_hash(sysdate, 'SHA1'  )  sha1_explicit,
   standard_hash(sysdate, 'SHA256')  sha256,
   standard_hash(sysdate, 'SHA384')  sha384,
   standard_hash(sysdate, 'SHA512')  sha512,
   standard_hash(sysdate, 'MD5'   )  md5
from
   dual;
code }

Note that the second parameter must be in uppercase, otherwise an → development/databases/Oracle/errors/ORA-00904_invalid-identifier error is thrown.

sa:
 `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/functions/ora/hash`
